# Start tmux:
tmux

# Detach from tmux:
Ctrl-b d

# Restore tmux session:
tmux attach

# Detach an already attached session (great if you are moving devices with different screen resolutions)
tmux attach -d 

# Display session:
tmux ls

# Start a shared session:
tmux -S /tmp/your_shared_session
chmod 777 /tmp/your_shared_session

# Help screen (Q to quit):
Ctrl-b ?

# Scroll in window:
Ctrl-b PageUp/PageDown

# Reload configuation file
Ctrl-b : source-file /path/to/file

# Window management
# =================

# Create window:
Ctrl-b c

# Destroy window:
Ctrl-b x

# Switch between windows:
Ctrl-b [0-9]
or
Ctrl-b Arrows

# Split windows horizontally:
Ctrl-b %

# Split windows vertically:
Ctrl-b "



# vim tmux integration 
ctrl hjkl

#copy paste in vi mode
https://awhan.wordpress.com/2010/06/20/copy-paste-in-tmux/

1) enter copy mode using Control+b [
2) navigate to beginning of text, you want to select and hit Space
3) move around using arrow keys to select region
4) when you reach end of region simply hit Enter to copy the region
5) now Control+b ] will paste the selection


also can be done with mouse , ctr a + m (mouse on), then select with mouse, ctr p , ou ctr P 
see https://github.com/gpakosz/.tmux


# 
ctrl b  # for remote
ctrl a  # for local 


# fullscreen / zoom
ctrl a/b z
